item.title: Please Help
item.dc:creator: @Jordiescape Jordiescape
item.description:
@Jordiescape wrote:

Tonypker, are you fucking retarded? The error is basically telling you what’s causing it.

[quote author=Yz85Racer link=topic=304725.msg2442870#msg2442870 date=1221542889]

[quote=“ziplock, post:3, topic:231372”]No it means he added a extra space or tab in one of his .cfg files…i have experienced this before
always backup your files…especially .cfg files[/quote]
You and tonypker13 are absolutely fucking stupid. Trigger is right, that exception is thrown to indicate the JVM has been told to access a class which does not exist. You should really take a look at the API sometime:

Thrown if the Java Virtual Machine or a ClassLoader instance tries to load in the definition of a class (as part of a normal method call or as part of creating a new instance using the new expression) and no definition of the class could be found.

The searched-for class definition existed when the currently executing class was compiled, but the definition can no longer be found.


Owned lulz.
